    <h1><a href="/news/Cases-and-Cooling/Corsair-H105-AiO-watercooler-double-fans-hold-lights">Corsair H105 AiO watercooler - double the fans, hold the lights!</a></h1>
    <h2>Subject: <a href="/subject/cases-and-cooling">Cases and Cooling</a> | February 18, 2015 - 05:39 PM | <a href="/users/Jeremy-Hellstrom" rel="author">Jeremy Hellstrom</a><br />
     Tagged: <a href="/category/tags/corsair">corsair</a>, <a href="/category/tags/h105">H105</a></h2>
        <p>Last April <a href="http://www.pcper.com/reviews/Cases-and-Cooling/Corsair-H105-Extreme-Performance-Liquid-CPU-Cooler-Review">Sebastian reviewed Corsair&#39;s H105 AiO</a> watercooler granting it a Gold Award for its performance and the ease of installation.&nbsp; It has been almost a year and during that year a lot of new AiO watercoolers have arrived on the market so <a href="http://www.hardocp.com/article/2015/02/10/corsair_h105_240mm_extreme_perf_aio_cpu_cooler_review">it is worth popping by [H]ard|OCP </a>to see how this cooler stacks up against the new competition.&nbsp; It is <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00HKEI3EY/?tag=pcper04-20">still selling for around $110</a> and remains at the top of the charts for its cooling ability, unfortunately it also remains near the top of the dBA lists as well for those of you wanting a quiet system.&nbsp; The overall performance of the cooler, especially on overclocked processors helps it retain its Gold standing but keep an eye out for the new Corsair H110i GT AiO which you should be hearing about soon!</p>
<p class="rtecenter"><div class = "center-article-image"><a href="/news/Cases-and-Cooling/Corsair-H105-AiO-watercooler-double-fans-hold-lights" class="inline-image-link" title="View: 1420032041o3rmje1xpl_1_1.jpg"><img src="/files/imagecache/article_min_width/news/2015-02-18/1420032041o3rmje1xpl_1_1.jpg" alt="1420032041o3rmje1xpl_1_1.jpg" title="1420032041o3rmje1xpl_1_1.jpg"  class="pcper-inline" width="460" height="243" /></a></div></p>
